Combine 1 cup brown sugar, cornstarch, pumpkin pie spice, salt, and pumpkin. Stir in milk and eggs. Pour into pastry shell. Filling is generous--crimp edges high. Bake at 400 degrees F (205 degrees C) for 40 minutes. Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients - 1 Tablespoon brown sugar, butter or margarine, flour, walnuts, and orange peel. Remove pie from oven, and spoon this nut mixture over pie. Return pie to oven, and bake 5 - 10 minutes more. Remove from oven and let cool.